Germany Reiterates Rejection of Euro Bonds After Reding Proposal

-- B y   P a t r i c k   D o n a h u e
-- 
2011-09-23T10:00:24Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-09-23/germany-reiterates-rejection-of-euro-bonds-after-reding-proposal.html
Germany  reiterated its rejection of
jointly issued euro-area bonds in response to a proposal by
European Union Justice Commissioner Viviane Reding for joint
bonds backed by the six EU members with a AAA rating.   “Our position hasn’t changed,” Finance Ministry spokesman
Martin Kreienbaum told reporters today in Berlin.   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Patrick Donahue at 
 pdonahue1@bloomberg.net  